{"search_data": "Central scholarships.gov.in \u2013 Post Matric Scholarship Scheme Online Application for MinoritiesTable of Contents  Post Matric Scholarship Scheme 2018 Application Form for MinoritiesPost Matric Minority Scholarship Eligibility CriteriaPost Matric Scholarship 2018-19 \u2013 Duration & Rate of ScholarshipReferencesPost Matric Scholarship Scheme 2018 Application Form for MinoritiesBelow is the complete procedure to apply online for Post Matric Scholarship 2018 for Minorities:-Visit the National Scholarship Portal at scholarships.gov.inAt homepage, go to \u201cCentral Schemes\u201d section and click at \u201cMinistry of Minority Affairs\u201d sub-section. Then click at \u201cApply\u201d link in front of \u2018Post Matric Scholarships Scheme for Minorities\u2019 or directly click this linkThen the Post Matric Minority Scholarship 2018 Login Page will appear as follows:-Post Matric Minority Scholarship LoginThen click at \u201cNew Student ? Register Here\u201d link and then the Post Matric Scholarship Scheme Registration Guidelines will appear as follows:-Post Matric Scholarship Scheme Registration GuidelinesRead the instructions and click at \u201cContinue\u201d button to open the Post Matric Scholarship Registration Form:-Post Matric Scholarship Registration FormFill the essential details, click at the \u201cRegister\u201d button to get Username and ID on your registered Mobile Number.After candidates can \u201cLogin\u201d using the details sent on Mobile number, Verify OTP, Change Password and then click at the \u201cApply\u201d link on the dashboard to fill the Post Matric Scholarship 2018 Online Application Form which will appear as follows:-Post Matric Scholarship 2018 Application FormFill all the details and click at the \u201cSave & Continue\u201d button to complete the online application process for Post Matric Scholarship Scheme 2018-19.This scheme focuses on Minorities Empowerment through education and will lead to upliftment of socio economic conditions of the students from minority communities.Post Matric Minority Scholarship Eligibility CriteriaAny eligible student studying in Class 1st to 10th in any govt. or private school can apply for the Post-Matric Scholarship Scheme. Eligibility Criteria for Post Matric Minority Scholarship is mentioned below:-Applicants must have secured at-least 50% marks or equivalent in the previous final examination.Applicant must belong to the minority community.Annual income of the family of the applicant from all sources must not exceed Rs. 2 lakh per annum.Pre Post Matric Scholarship MinoritiesMuslims, Sikhs, Christians, Buddhists, Jains and Zoroastrians (Parsis) have been notified as minority communities. Moreover, 30% of scholarships will be earmarked for girl students.Post Matric Scholarship 2018-19 \u2013 Duration & Rate of ScholarshipGovt. will provide Post Matric Scholarship 2018 for the entire course duration. However, maintenance allowance is only given for 10 months in an academic year. The rate of Scholarship is given below:- Post Matric Scholarship 2018 AmountItemHostellersDay ScholarsAdmission and tuition fee for classes XI and XIIRs. 7,000 p.aRs. 7000 p.aAdmission and Tuition fee for technical and vocational courses of XI and XII (including fees / charges for raw materials)Rs. 10,000 p.aRs. 10000 p.aTuition & Admission Fees for Under-graduate & Post Graduate CoursesRs. 3,000 p.aRs. 3000 p.aMaintenance Allowance for Class XI and XII including technical and vocational coursesRs. 380 p.mRs. 230 p.mMaintenance Allowance for courses other than technical and professional courses at UG and PG levelRs. 570 p.mRs. 300 p.mMaintenance Allowance for M.Phil and Ph.DRs. 1200 p.mRs. 550 p.mState Government / Union Territory administration will implement this scholarship scheme. To get all the details, click at the link \u2013 Post Matric Scholarship 2018 Scheme DetailsReferences\u2014 In case of any query, candidates can see Frequently Asked Questions \u2013 FAQ\u2019s